      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Federal Lands Infrastructure Partnership Act or the FLIP Act</b></p> <p>This bill extends through FY2022, and revises allocations from, the Land and Water Conservation Fund.</p> <p>The bill makes allocations available from the fund&nbsp;for the Payment In-Lieu of Taxes Program. This program compensates local governments for tax revenue lost due to tax-exempt federal lands within their boundaries. </p> <p>Allocations shall be made available from the fund through FY2024 to promote offshore energy exploration, innovation, and education.</p> <p>The Department of the Interior shall carry out a federal energy permit streamlining pilot program for the outer Continental Shelf.</p> <p>The bill directs Interior to: (1) establish an Offshore Energy Innovation Hub; (2) award offshore energy innovation grants to institutions of higher education; and (3) prepare a list of the science, technology, engineering, and math-related academic fields that address current and future workforce needs for offshore energy-related activities. </p>]]></text>
